        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pastry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the {{plain-flour}} (for the pastry), {{fine-sea-salt}}, and {{caster-sugar}} (for the pastry) in a large bowl. Add the cold {{unsalted-butter}} and rub in quickly until the mixture resembles rough crumbs with some pea-sized pieces of butter visible. Add 5 to 7 tablespoons of ice-cold water, one at a time, mixing with a fork until the dough just comes together. Divide into two equal pieces, flatten into discs, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Peel, core, and slice the {{bramley-apples}}. In a large bowl, toss them with the {{caster-sugar}} (for the filling) and the {{lemon-juice}}. Sprinkle over the {{plain-flour}} (for thickening), the {{ground-cinnamon}}, and the {{ground-nutmeg}}. Mix until the slices are evenly coated.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Line and fill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Roll one pastry disc on a floured surface to 3 mm thick. Line the pie dish, leaving 2 cm overhang. Fill with the apple mixture, pile it high, it will cook down. Roll the second disc and lay over the top. Press the edges together, trim, and crimp. Cut four vents in the top.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Glaze and bake, 50 to 55 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brush the top with the beaten {{free-range-eggs}} and sprinkle with {{demerara-sugar}}. Bake on the lower-middle shelf at 200°C fan for 20 minutes, then reduce to 180°C fan and bake for a further 30 to 35 minutes until the pastry is deep golden and the filling is bubbling through the vents. Rest for at least 1 hour before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
